Congress is debating the constitutionally questionable issue of
whether or not to count illegal aliens in the 1990 census.
Congressional House seats are apportioned to the states and huge sums
of federal money are allocated based on census population.
California, with an estimated half of our illegal aliens, will be
greatly affected.</SUM>
